_Pa’al_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pa’al_ past tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                            | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | כָּתַבְתִּי<br>_kosavti_<br>I wrote | \< | כָּתַבְנוּ<br>_kosavnu_<br>We wrote | \< |
| *Second-Person* | כָּתַבְתָּ <br>_kosavto_<br> You [male] wrote | כָּתַבְתְּ <br>_kosavt_<br> You [female] wrote  | כְּתַבְתֶּם <br>_ksavtem_<br> You [males] wrote  | כְּתַבְתֶּן <br>_ksavten_<br> You [females] wrote  |
| *Third-Person* | כָּתַב <br>_kausav_<br> He wrote | כָּתְבָה <br>_kausvau_<br> She wrote  | כָּתְבוּ <br>_kausvu_<br> They [male or female] wrote  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ת, and ב above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
